<br>
However in ST, you all remember those aged caretakers or whatever in the library? Ok good, keep those in mind.<br>
<br>
Remember that patch a while ago making NPC/mobs more selective in their spell choices?  Ok good, keep that in mind.<br>
<br>
Prior to the zone change those mobs were nuking for 1600 and love to chain cast.  Keep that in mind.<br>
<br>
Now with the zone change, they removed those things from the library and added them in clusters in different parts of the zone.  Did I mention they like to cast as soon as you're spotted?  <br>
<br>
Upon initial agro, cluster of mobs, chain casting sunstrike.<br>
<br>
If that doesn't get your heart racing, then you can run by the clusters of specs that HT for 1k+ and have a lifedraw proc.<br>
<br>
Throw in a few mobs that AE, nuke, tap, HT, hit hard, etc.....well you have your work cut out for you.<br>
<br>
Even if you survive the gauntlet, you still will have to take the plung into the icy/freezing water guarded by a mob, then drop down again into the final tunnel.  200 Safefall will not save you from taking dmg here.<br>
<br>
I'm not saying it can't be done.  I'm sure it can.  In fact, I want to see this.  I want to see any class race do this run fully spawned from the zone in through the FA gate.<br>
<br>
I'm not sure what prize can be awarded, but I want to see this done.  No bard speed, no DA idols, just pure run for your life sprint down to the FA in under 1 hour.  Nothing but pure fun and fear. <p>Macgee
